node.text:
I get this question all the time. When Algae grows on them, which happens pretty fast because they are textured to promote Algae growth they really shine. Baitfish hang out and feed on the Algae, in turn bigger fish hang out to feed on the baitfish.

@mossbackhabitat

node.text: Fishing is just fun, no matter what you catch or how big. Being out on the water is just plain peaceful. This post front day I was fishing slough’s off of flats. Just a little deeper water but still they were hard to come by. Some are spawning now and some are done. Never found the pile of fish I was looking for, but there’s always tomorrow! Happy fishing everyone!

node.text:
The wedge shape pushes water down on the blade so you can crawl around spider rigging. Matched with the  @crappiemagnet Slab curly with the tail that works at .3 mph it’s a deadly combination. They preferred these more than the Crappie magnet tipped with a minnow this day. Course it never hurts to know where your @mossbackhabitat are!!
.

.
